    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-03-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-03-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="880"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d880">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.00/8695</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Messersmith</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 7</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-03-09">March 9,
                            1940</date>.<lb/>[Received March 11.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report that ex-President
                    Menocal endeavored yesterday, through an intermediary in whom I have complete
                    confidence, to ascertain from me whether the Government of the United States
                    would like him to join forces with Colonel Batista or with Dr. Grau.<note n="13"
                        xml:id="d880fn1">Ramon Grau San Martin, Provisional President of Cuba,
                        September 1933–January 1934.</note> General Menocal also expressed to the
                    same intermediary his belief that Colonel Batista would resign his candidacy if
                    he received an indication that this would be pleasing to the Government of the
                    United States.</p>
                <p>Needless to say, I am taking no step which might indicate that the Government of
                    the United States has any desire with reference to the group with which General
                    Menocal may associate himself, or concerning Colonel Batista’s candidacy.</p>
                <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">George S. Messersmith</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
